cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.EC. 

The paper deals with the problem of scheduling advertisers to sponsored search slots, which involves both optimization and game-theoretic considerations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and data structures (DS) in the context of the auction mechanism. The use of a descending-price auction and a machine scheduling problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the categories of machine learning (LG) and economics (EC).
